=== Dissemination of course innovations <course_output>

This is a selection of the outputs related to the innovation of the lab courses.

- #cite(<pols2020physics>, form: "prose"): _A Physics Lab Course in Times of COVID-19_.
- #cite(<pols2024redesigning>, form: "prose"): _Redesigning a first year physics lab course on the basis of the procedural and conceptual knowledge in science model_.
- #cite(<pols2021students>, form: "prose"): _Students' report on an open inquiry_.
- #cite(<pols2023one>, form: "prose"): _One setup for many experiments: enabling versatile student-led investigations_.
- #cite(<pols2024elements>, form: "prose"): _Elements of proper conclusion_.
- #cite(<pols2021differences>, form: "prose") _Comparison of practicum courses across four universities_
- #cite(<pols2024vitruvian>, form: "prose"): _The Vitruvian man: An introduction to measurement and data analysis_.

